  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground paprika</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>smoky fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-doner-with-sweet-chilli-sauce-and-smoky-fries/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fries are cooking, peel and chop your<strong> red onion[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Chop<strong> half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining chopped onion</strong> finely and set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-doner-with-sweet-chilli-sauce-and-smoky-fries/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and finely shred</p><p>Slice your<strong> tomato[es] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-doner-with-sweet-chilli-sauce-and-smoky-fries/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>halloumi </strong>into thick strips</p><p>Add the <strong>halloumi strips</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>onion petals</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, the <strong>remaining ground paprika</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Mix it all together until the halloumi and onion are well coated – these are your<strong> spiced halloumi strips & onion petals</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-doner-with-sweet-chilli-sauce-and-smoky-fries/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non stick) over a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> spiced halloumi strips & onion petals</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min, turning the halloumi<strong> </strong>halfway, or until it is golden on all sides and the onion has slightly softened – this is your <strong>halloumi doner</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-doner-with-sweet-chilli-sauce-and-smoky-fries/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the halloumi is cooking, combine your<strong> red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>– this is your <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-doner-with-sweet-chilli-sauce-and-smoky-fries/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fries are almost done, remove the tray[s] from the oven and top the fries with your <strong>wholemeal pitta[s]</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-doner-with-sweet-chilli-sauce-and-smoky-fries/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the<strong> warmed pitta </strong>with the <strong>halloumi doner </strong>and some of the<strong> shredded lettuce</strong>,<strong> sliced onion </strong>and <strong>tomato wedges</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>sweet</strong> <strong>chilli sauce</strong>, garnish with the <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>smoky fries</strong> and <strong>remaining shredded lettuce</strong>,<strong> onion slices </strong>and <strong>tomato wedges</strong> to the side and drizzle with a little <strong>olive oil </strong>and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
